item.content:encoded:

Course Description

This session discusses the 6 basics to effective healing, how to implement those basics and the importance of implementing evidence-based wound care approaches.

Certification

Provider approved by the California Board of Registered Nursing, Provider Number 14269, for 1.0 contact hours. Infinitus, LLC is an approved Illinois Physical Therapy Continuing Education Sponsor, License number 216.000207.  This course is approved for 1 CEH’s.

At the conclusion of this program, the participant will be able to:

  •     Discuss different ways to implement the basics of wound healing.
  •     Recognize the importance of evidence-based wound care approaches.

item.title: When the Foot Hits the Ground Everything Changes
item.dc:creator: Bill Richlen
item.content:encoded:
Course Description

This session will discuss the effects of normal weight bearing on foot structures in comparison to how neuropathy and loss of proprioception affects the feet of diabetics. Treatment options including proper footwear and gait training with offloading vs. non-weightbearing will be explored to determine the best way to promote healing and prevent ulcers.

Certification

Provider approved by the California Board of Registered Nursing, Provider Number 14269, for 1.0 contact hours. Infinitus, LLC is an approved Illinois Physical Therapy Continuing Education Sponsor, License number 216.000207.  This course is approved for 1 CEH’s.

Objectives

At the conclusion of this program, the participant will be able to:
  •       Discuss foot anatomy and gait mechanics. 
  •       Recognize the effects of neuropathy and foot deformities.
  •       Identify different types of shoe modifications and offloading methods.

item.title: Compression Made Easy
item.dc:creator: Denise Richlen
item.content:encoded:
Course Description

Provider approved by the California Board of Registered Nursing, Provider Number 14269, for 1.0 contact hours. Infinitus, LLC is an approved Illinois Physical Therapy Continuing Education Sponsor, License number 216.000207.  This course is approved for 1 CEH’s.

At the conclusion of this program, the participant will be able to:

  •     Discuss the different types of seating and positioning equipment.
  •     Describe the different postural concerns of the pelvis and spine, common seating problems and how to correct them.

item.title: What’s Therapy Got To Do With Wound Care
item.dc:creator: Denise Richlen
item.content:encoded:
Course Description

This session will discuss the roles of each therapy discipline in managing wounds, their role as a member of the interdisciplinary team, and the modalities that they can incorporate into their treatment plan to improve wound healing outcomes.

Certification

Provider approved by the California Board of Registered Nursing, Provider Number 14269, for 1.0 contact hours. Infinitus, LLC is an approved Illinois Physical Therapy Continuing Education Sponsor, License number 216.000207.  This course is approved for 1 CEH’s.

Objectives

At the conclusion of this program, the participant will be able to:
  • Describe 3 roles Physical/Occupational Therapy/Speech Therapy have with wound care patients.
  • Discuss the role of Physical/Occupational/Speech Therapy in the wound care interdisciplinary team.
  • List the adjunctive modalities that Physical/Occupational Therapy can provide to enhance healing.
